(9619, 1, '2013-06-10 13:18:17', '2013-06-10 13:18:17', '[spb_parallax bg_image="10229" bg_type="cover" alt_background="none" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]\n<h1><span style="color: #ffffff;">"Functionality and detail are meticulously harmonised with versatility and durability to strike exactly the right balance."</span></h1>\n[/spb_parallax] [blank_spacer height="20px" width="1/1" el_position="first last"] [spb_text_block pb_margin_bottom="no" pb_border_bottom="no" width="1/3" el_position="first"]\n\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-10263" alt="mismo_logo3_project" src="http://localhost:8888/annujmah/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/mismo_logo3_project.jpg" width="580" height="320" />\n\n&nbsp;\n\nFirmly based in the Danish design tradition and appreciation for the values of classic craftsmanship, Mismo unites natural materials with simple yet refined details to create products of true style. Leather constitutes the backbone of Mismo design, and only the best materials of premium quality are used.\n\nFunctionality and detail are meticulously harmonised with versatility and durability to strike exactly the right balance.\n\n[/spb_text_block] [spb_single_image image="ype-of-10259" image_size="full" frame="noframe" full_width="no" lightbox="no" link_target="_self" width="1/3"] [spb_single_image image="ype-of-10266" image_size="full" frame="noframe" full_width="no" lightbox="no" link_target="_self" width="1/3" el_position="last"] [blank_spacer height="50px" width="1/1" el_position="first last"] [divider type="thin" text="Go to top" full_width="yes" width="1/1" el_position="first last"] [blank_spacer height="50px" width="1/1" el_position="first last"] [spb_single_image image="10265" image_size="full" frame="noframe" full_width="no" lightbox="no" link_target="_self" caption="The new Mismo rucksack for 2013." width="1/2" el_position="first"] [spb_single_image image="10260" image_size="full" frame="noframe" full_width="no" lightbox="no" link_target="_self" caption="The new Mismo accessories range." width="1/2" el_position="last"] [spb_parallax title="HOW IT ALL BEGAN" bg_image="10269" bg_type="cover" alt_background="none" el_class="bt0 bb0" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]\n<h2 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #ffffff;"><span style="color: #000000;">Danish bag-maker<a href="http://www.mismo.dk/" target="_blank"><span style="color: #000000;">Mismo</span></a>was founded 10 years ago by husband-and-wife duo Alexander Bach [decorative_ampersand]&amp;[/decorative_ampersand]Rikke Overgaard, before the notion of the minimal everyday bag became so popular. "I think the reason you might say we develop great bags consistently is because we have this very steady platform from where the design and idiom originates," explains Bach, pointing out that the inspiration for each new line builds on what they''ve done in the past.</span>\n</span></h2>\n[/spb_parallax] [blank_spacer height="20px" width="1/1" el_position="first last"] [spb_single_image image="10268" image_size="full" frame="noframe" full_width="no" lightbox="no" link_target="_self" caption="The new Mismo collection for Autumn / Winter 2013." width="1/1" el_position="first last"] [spb_text_block pb_margin_bottom="yes" pb_border_bottom="no" el_class="mt0 pt0" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]\n\n[hr]\n\n[/spb_text_block] [spb_text_block pb_margin_bottom="no" pb_border_bottom="no" width="1/3" el_position="first"]\n\n[dropcap1]T[/dropcap1]he spirit of its designers infuses Mismo bags with a real depth of pure function and stripped-down essentials, bags which shrug off frills in favor of continually evolving material selection and intelligent use of color. For Spring 2013, Mismo brings its own unique mustard yellow back into the fray, first seen in 2009 in a collaboration with<a href="http://www.stormfashion.dk/" target="_blank">Storm</a>.\n\n[/spb_text_block] [spb_text_block pb_margin_bottom="no" pb_border_bottom="no" width="1/3"]\n\n"It''s funny because brighter colors don''t sell well generally," says Bach, revealing what''s perhaps a counterintuitive strategy for a modern designer. "The mustard color, for instance, we already know won''t sell well but it draws a lot of attention to what we''re doing and is authentic to who we are. Finding the right balance of colors is like creating your own painting. It''s a delicate process."\n\n[/spb_text_block] [spb_text_block pb_margin_bottom="no" pb_border_bottom="no" width="1/3" el_position="last"]\n\nThe new line features interesting new materials for Mismo, which have been developed over a prolonged period of time. There''s a floral nubuck leather, which has been embossed with a botanical print before being hand-dyed and brushed for a more broken-in feel. There''s also denim sourced from Limonta that shares a similar perfectly worn feel to the touch.\n\n[/spb_text_block] [blank_spacer height="50px" width="1/1" el_position="first last"] [spb_gmaps address="Copenhagen, Denmark" size="400" type="roadmap" zoom="9" pin_image="10270" fullscreen="yes" el_class="bt0 bb0" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]', 'Mismo - Briefcase', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'mismo-briefcase', '', '', '2013-06-10 13:18:17', '2013-06-10 13:18:17', '', 0, 'http://neighborhood.swiftideas.net/?post_type=product&#038;p=9619', 0, 'product', '', 0),
